Angry Khayelitsha residents have torched the house of Mrwetyana’s alleged killer. The UCT student was raped and killed. It's alleged a post office worker confessed to the crime. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Angry Khayelitsha residents have torched the house of Uyinene Mrwetyana's alleged killer. The UCT student was raped and killed. It's alleged a post office worker confessed to the crime. READ: Students vow UCT shutdown Cape Town's fire and rescue services were prevented from performing their duties and forced to leave the area. UCT students are now vowing to shut down the university over security issues. The protesting students are demanding that security on campus be boosted. They have given the university a deadline to respond to the demand.